The paper presents a model for supervised classification using a recurrent encoder and linear decoders, trained via backpropagation-through-time. The model is designed to exhibit the power of deep networks while reducing the number of trainable parameters. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on image classification (specifically, using the MNIST dataset), cs.CV is more likely to be the second most relevant sub-category after cs.LG.
